feat(ui): responsive polish — mobile back-to-globe, compact simulator cards, blur-reveal motion on risk/enterprise

Map
- /map Back-to-Globe pill now has a 44px tap target, safe-area-inset
  bottom/left padding so it clears the iOS home indicator, and a
  subtle transition-in so it reads on phone-sized viewports as well
  as desktop. Still auto-hides while Street View is up.

Simulator
- ScenarioCard collapses by default on mobile to a single-row
  magnitude pill (top-left of the pano) with a tap-to-expand
  header. Desktop layout unchanged.
- QuestionCard drops the survival pie from 140px to 96px on mobile,
  trims padding 24 to 14, and shrinks question/option text + gaps
  so the 360 panorama stays visible underneath.

Home hero
- Hero chip, headline, rule, and Demo CTA now use a slower
  ~1.1s blur-reveal cascade (q-blur-reveal + delay 1..4) to match
  the reference cinematic reveal language.
- Mobile flying transform lands the globe at EXACT (0,0) — true
  card-centre — at scale 1.4 so it fits inside the card without
  being cropped. Desktop stays at 1.55 punch.

Risk + Enterprise reveal language
- New .q-blur-reveal (blur 10 to 0, y 22 to 0, 1.1s ease-out-quint)
  and .q-rule (width 0 to 100%) CSS primitives in globals.css, plus
  a Framer-Motion Reveal/RevealGroup/RevealItem helper for
  stagger-on-scroll without per-call boilerplate. Respects
  prefers-reduced-motion.
- Applied entrance motion to: /risk, /risk/results (Assessment
  Report header), /enterprise/login, /enterprise/dashboard
  (KPI cards + table), /enterprise/risk-assessment (KPIs + CTAs),
  /enterprise/building/hss hero card. Animations borrow only the
  motion style from the reference snippets — layouts unchanged.

Stability
- npx tsc --noEmit: clean
- npx next build: all 16 routes generated successfully
